    <string name="c30_manual_auto_intro_title">Auto scroll and manual scroll</string>
    <string name="c30_manual_auto_intro_body">In manual scroll mode, go to the top of the page and tap "Start" to capture the first screen automatically. Scroll down half a screen to one screen at a time; each screen is captured when scrolling stops. At the bottom, tap "Done" to stitch all screens into one long screenshot. You do not need to tap Capture repeatedly. \n\n In auto scroll mode, the WhiteYun Screenshot accessibility service scrolls the page and captures it automatically.</string>
    <string name="c30_speed_mode_intro_title">About speed mode</string>
    <string name="c30_speed_mode_intro_body">Speed mode improves the speed and accuracy of stitching vertical screenshots, so it is recommended. \n\n Disable it when stitching horizontal screenshots or when you do not want overlapping areas removed.</string>
    <string name="c30_auto_scroll_intro_title">About auto scroll</string>
    <string name="c30_auto_scroll_intro_body">On Android 7.0 and later, WhiteYun Screenshot can scroll the screen automatically using its accessibility service. Enable it under "Settings - Accessibility - WhiteYun Screenshot". \n\nWhen you tap "Start", the page scrolls down automatically and a red line appears. Tap anywhere above the red line to stop the screenshot.</string>
    <string name="c30_red_line_hint">Tap above the red line to stop the screenshot</string>
